This is the polished version of the i3resizemode script i made in one of the Lets Linux episodes. I named it after the moderator on up who banned me for a month after I told a guy to RTFM&hellip;
i3Kornhe - Resize windows by moving the corners. SYNOPSIS i3Kornhe [-v|-h] DIRECTION
DESCRIPTION The script checks if the currently active window is floating. If it is floating the script will acrivate one of four modes depending on the direction.
